						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the Mahāliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kalachurya-chakravarti Bhujabalamalla.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription refers itself to the reign of Kalachurya-chakravarti Bhujabalamalla. The Śaka year is lost. The extant details are Paushya śu. 11, Monday, Uttarāyaṇa saṅkramaṇa.</p>						

						<p>It records the grant of the village Koṁḍanūr situated in the Kuṁdurge-kaṁpaṇa of Kūṁḍi Three Thousand for offerings <hi rend="italic">etc.,</hi> to god Taṭēśvara of Mahātīrtha by the king's officer <hi rend="italic">Pergaḍe</hi> Dhannugidēva in conjunction with the Karṇas, with the consent of the king. Amṛitarāsi was the recipient of the gift.</p>						

						</summary>
